#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.15"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.15:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.15:0.2"
msgid "2. Sīhanādavagga"
msgstr "2. The Lion’s Roar"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 15. Gaṇḍasutta → gaṇḍopamasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.15:0.3"
msgid "15. Gaṇḍasutta"
msgstr "15. The Simile of the Boil"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.15:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṇḍo anekavassagaṇiko."
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose there was a boil that was many years old."

msgctxt "an9.15:1.2"
msgid "Tassassu gaṇḍassa nava vaṇamukhāni nava abhedanamukhāni."
msgstr "And that boil had nine orifices that were continually open wounds."

msgctxt "an9.15:1.3"
msgid "Tato yaṃ kiñci pagghareyya—"
msgstr "Whatever oozed out of them"

#. VAR: jegucchiyaṃyeva → jegucchiyeva (mr)
msgctxt "an9.15:1.4"
msgid ""
"asuciyeva pagghareyya, duggandhaṃyeva pagghareyya, jegucchiyaṃyeva "
"pagghareyya;"
msgstr "would be filthy, stinking, and disgusting."

msgctxt "an9.15:1.5"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci pasaveyya—"
msgstr "Whatever leaked out them"

msgctxt "an9.15:1.6"
msgid ""
"asuciyeva pasaveyya, duggandhaṃyeva pasaveyya, jegucchiyaṃyeva pasaveyya."
msgstr "would be filthy, stinking, and disgusting."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.387"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: cātumahābhūtikassa → cātummahābhūtikassa (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.15:2.1"
msgid ""
"Gaṇḍoti kho, bhikkhave, imassetaṃ cātumahābhūtikassa kāyassa adhivacanaṃ "
"mātāpettikasambhavassa odanakummāsūpacayassa "
"aniccucchādanaparimaddanabhedanaviddhaṃsanadhammassa."
msgstr ""
"‘Boil’ is a term for this body made up of the four primary elements, "
"produced by mother and father, built up from rice and porridge, liable to "
"impermanence, to wearing away and erosion, to breaking up and destruction."

msgctxt "an9.15:2.2"
msgid "Tassassu gaṇḍassa nava vaṇamukhāni nava abhedanamukhāni."
msgstr "And that boil has nine orifices that were continually open wounds."

msgctxt "an9.15:2.3"
msgid "Tato yaṃ kiñci paggharati—"
msgstr "Whatever oozed out of them"

msgctxt "an9.15:2.4"
msgid ""
"asuciyeva paggharati, duggandhaṃyeva paggharati, jegucchiyaṃyeva paggharati;"
msgstr "is filthy, stinking, and disgusting."

msgctxt "an9.15:2.5"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci pasavati—"
msgstr "Whatever leaks out of them"

msgctxt "an9.15:2.6"
msgid "asuciyeva pasavati, duggandhaṃyeva pasavati, jegucchiyaṃyeva pasavati."
msgstr "is filthy, stinking, and disgusting."

msgctxt "an9.15:2.7"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ kāye nibbindathā”ti."
msgstr "So, mendicants, have no illusion about this body.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.15:2.8"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
